    "body": "If you want an easy chain, use a PoA one, not PoW. Then you don't have to care about difficulties and whatnot. If you only need to run on a single machine you can use `geth --dev`. This uses ephemeral datadirs and accounts, but you can make them persistent via specifying `--datadir /path/to/your/data`.\r\n\r\n`eth.gasPrice` is a suggestion based on the past transaction prices. If all the transactions you made were priced around 18gwei (or you didn't make any), it won't suggest anything lower. Send a bunch of 0 priced transactions manually and it should pick it up. Though take care, Geth by default rejects forwarding 0 priced transactions to prevent DoS attacks.",
